
                          Selenium & Ruby using Cucumber

  What is it?
  -----------
  This is a demo of Selenium & Ruby using Cucumber.


  The Latest Version
  ------------------
  https://github.com/yes4me?tab=repositories
  Started on: Sep 26, 2015


  Documentation
  -------------
  Explication of the code is: <pending>


  Installation
  ------------
  install Ruby
  At the command prompt, run:
		cmd > gem update --system
		cmd > gem install cucumber
		cmd > gem install cucumber --no-rdoc --no-ri
		cmd > gem install rspec --no-rdoc --no-ri
		cmd > gem install selenium-webdriver --no-rdoc --no-ri
		cmd > gem list
  For Windows, download Ansicon (for color output on command prompt):
		https://github.com/adoxa/ansicon/downloads
		cmd > ansicon.exe -i
  Create the project:
		create a directtory
		Go to the directory
		cmd > cucumber --init
	Run the project (pick either of the following):
		cmd > cucumber
		cmd > cucumber -qt -t @<tag name>
		cmd > cucumber -p <profileName>
		PS: profiles are like suit, and are saved in "cucumber.yml"


